Do you not suspect. reader, whence and wherefore this fable was invented? namely, when the brightness of the Christian sabbath was now risen, and increased every day, they had recourse to these monsters either of magio or of fables, whereby the glory of our sabbath might be obscured, and that of the Jews exalted. The various, and indeed con- trary relations of historians bring the truth of the story into suspicion.
